        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3326651324" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16068626981997294280">Mr. Darcy finds himself vexed by Elizabeth. But since he has been rejected he can not build the relationship any further. So, to work out his frustrations he sits down and writes letters to Elizabeth. The catch is that he never mails them.<br/><br/>The letters show the continued development of his infatuation turned love for the young woman. It also shows his frustration over her rejection of him. It further develops what his feelings are as he is stymied at every turn.<br/><br/>It is a unique way to develop his ch</span>
  <span id="freeText16068626981997294280" style="display:none">Mr. Darcy finds himself vexed by Elizabeth. But since he has been rejected he can not build the relationship any further. So, to work out his frustrations he sits down and writes letters to Elizabeth. The catch is that he never mails them.<br /><br />The letters show the continued development of his infatuation turned love for the young woman. It also shows his frustration over her rejection of him. It further develops what his feelings are as he is stymied at every turn.<br /><br />It is a unique way to develop his character for the reader. It is a unique storyline and helps the reader to further understand the reasons for Darcy’s frustrations and desires.<br /><br />I don’t want to write anymore because that would have to give spoilers and I don’t want to spoil your reading of the story for yourself.<br /><br />Enjoy!</span>
  <a data-text-id="16068626981997294280" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
